                            <comment id="12856363" author="antheque" created="Tue, 13 Apr 2010 11:21:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;IMHO it would be a better idea to campaign for a compress 1.1 release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The trunk contains fixes to issues &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/COMPRESS-73&quot; title=&quot;ZipArchiveInputStream cannot handle some valid files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;COMPRESS-73&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;COMPRESS-73&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/COMPRESS-87&quot; title=&quot;ZipArchiveInputStream doesn&amp;#39;t report the end of a truncated archive&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;COMPRESS-87&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;COMPRESS-87&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/COMPRESS-89&quot; title=&quot;Better support for encrypted ZIP files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;COMPRESS-89&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;COMPRESS-89&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which are relevant to Aperture. We&apos;ve been using a snapshot version since last August.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a thread on commons-dev, Let&apos;s call for some &quot;Release early, release often&quot; &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12856841" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 14 Apr 2010 12:15:49 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Agreed, I&apos;ll keep an eye on dev@commons to see if I can help push out the release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12900213" author="jukkaz" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2010 09:26:17 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;In revision 987074 I upgraded Tika to use Commons Compress 1.1. That should solve this problem.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
